Our aim is to inspire resilient women to follow their dreams.
For many of us, those dreams turn into wishes. We intend to instill resilience and encourage women to do whatever it takes to make their dreams come true. We carried out a social experiment with Taapsee Pannu and we were quite surprised with the choices that women make. Here's our latest brand film.

'Garba' comes from 'Garbha' meaning 'Womb'
It is a festival that celebrates the Divine Feminine. There is divinity in all of us waiting to wake up to dance the divine cyclic dance symbolizing the cyclic nature of Existence. 
At Baggit, we celebrate the colour Red today. It is the colour of a Mother's Womb.
Bring out your deepest desires and bag them all in a bag that is worthy of holding your desires. Only on www.baggit.com!

And with "The Midas Touch" we sign off...
Kajal, like many women we know, couldn't just give up to her circumstances of declining health in the family and simply surrender herself to fate.
Undeterred by immediate reality, her mind became an inquisitive palace of creativity and mundane things that held no value to others, eventually became priceless with her touch. Such is the brilliance and beauty of life lived with an undefeated spirit!

As we bid adieu to this season, we hope we inspired you with these stories of our Resilient Fighters!
Until next time!
Till then stay strong, stay resilient!

#ForeverResilient #Resilience #Baggit #ResilientFightersForever #RFF
